OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1774285870
OL,3,CDomestic abuse victims to get better
OL,4,Ccourt support in #5m funding boost
OL,6,FDomestic abuse victims will be able to
OL,7,Fget better support as their cases pass
OL,8,Fthrough the courts, including pilot
OL,9,Fschemes in areas including Wiltshire,
OL,10,FHampshire, Dorset and the Isle of
OL,11,FWight.
OL,13,FIt's part of an announcement by the
OL,14,FGovernment to invest #5 million more
OL,15,Fin funding.
OL,17,FSolicitor General Ellie Reeves said
OL,18,Fthe Crown Prosecution Service would
OL,19,Fget the sum over two years to help
OL,20,Fvictims who have gone to the police
OL,21,Fabout domestic abuse.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
